1
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:34,560
I need to discuss something with you.

2
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:36,640
Go ahead.

3
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:40,520
It's about this portion of the cost.

4
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:41,880
Could you cover it upfront?

5
00:01:41,880 --> 00:01:43,960
I'll pay you back once we turn a profit.

6
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,400
See? What did I tell you?

7
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:48,680
You still want to get something for nothing.

8
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:49,520
So, will you do it or not?

9
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:51,960
What if you don't make any money?

10
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:53,200
What if you can't pay me back?

11
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:54,800
I'll pay you back.

12
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:56,360
Just paying me back isn't enough.

13
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:57,720
You'll owe me something extra.

14
00:01:57,720 --> 00:01:59,280
Hey, don't push your luck.

15
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:00,320
See?

16
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,360
You failed when it mattered most again.

17
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:04,400
Well...

18
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,680
I haven't figured it out yet.

19
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:09,840
Figured what out?

20
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,320
I just want you to help me test this boat.

21
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,600
See if it sinks or not.

22
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,320
Fine, I'll give it a try.

23
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,520
Let me tell everyone something.

24
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,280
Today,

25
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,840
we're scrapping the four themes we had.

26
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:27,560
And setting six new themes instead.

27
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,840
That means all of our

28
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:30,520
AR technology will be dropped.

29
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:32,760
The six themes include the Guofeng Theater,

30
00:02:32,760 --> 00:02:35,960
Ink Rhythm Battlefield, Paper Spirit Academy, Brush Tea Break,

31
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:38,560
Voice Actor House, and Paper & Ink Matchmaking Wall.

32
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,520
The spot where we're standing right now,

33
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,400
this is the Ink Rhythm Battlefield area.

34
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,480
With this new plan,

35
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:45,880
we've cut our costs by more than half.

36
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:47,080
And here,

37
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:49,200
we'd like to give special thanks to Comrade Xuan Yan.

38
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,440
Because these expenses

39
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,920
will be covered upfront by Comrade Xuan Yan.

40
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:53,680
A round of applause!

41
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,760
God Yan, you're amazing!

42
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:58,480
I'm not exactly thrilled about it.

43
00:02:58,480 --> 00:02:59,360
Amazing!

44
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:04,200
Wait, this Ink Rhythm Battlefield...

45
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,680
What's "Ink Rhythm"?

46
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:07,160
And what kind of battlefield is it?

47
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:10,360
Hold on, the battlefield will appear shortly.

48
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,880
Close enough. Done.

49
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,080
That's it?

50
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:42,080
No, no, I'm just asking.

51
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,840
You just reminded me.

52
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,760
There's one more step.

53
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:57,520
What you see before you

54
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,920
are our newly launched Ink Bombs.

55
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:02,120
Nine ninety-nine each.

56
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:07,360
So beautiful.

57
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:09,520
The Ink Bombs

58
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,800
are just our traffic drivers.

59
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,600
Our real profit product

60
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:13,680
is the auction.

61
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,880
Auction? An auction?

62
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:17,519
While visitors toss the Ink Bombs,

63
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:19,360
this massive Xuan paper painting

64
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,959
will keep transforming.

65
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,680
When they get an effect they like,

66
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,200
they can call stop.

67
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,680
That's when the auction begins.

68
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,600
Starting bid: 299.

69
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,600
Highest bidder wins.

70
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:31,960
Then

71
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,880
we swap in a new sheet.

72
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:38,720
So you're just hoping when it opens,

73
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,760
more suckers show up, right?

74
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:41,880
Director.

75
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:46,200
Director Liao, you'd better believe it.

76
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:49,080
I predict the biggest hit of the whole event,

77
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,360
and the top earner will be this setup.

78
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,840
I want to try.

79
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:56,760
Here.

80
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:58,360
I want to try too.

81
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:58,680
Here.

82
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,720
I want to try too.

83
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,720
Me, I'll try too.

84
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:03,040
Director Liao!

85
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,480
What a disgrace!

86
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:27,040
And this is the Paper & Ink Matchmaking Wall.

87
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,360
This setup uses just one board.

88
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,160
No, wait.

89
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:34,520
It's three boards.

90
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:36,520
Wang Hao, give me a hand.

91
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:38,520
We use three boards

92
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:41,080
to form this three-sided geometric wall.

93
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:42,960
Visitors who want to try matchmaking

94
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:45,720
can register with the attendant,

95
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:48,280
then take a verse or phrase they've thought of,

96
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:51,280
write it in ink on a paper screen,

97
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:52,760
and post it on this wall.

98
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:02,120
Four Treasures of the Study kit: 29.9.

99
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:02,880
That's right.

100
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:05,960
Then it waits for a kindred spirit

101
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,200
to write the matching couplet.

102
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,600
Once the original author approves,

103
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,440
the two of them can then

104
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:12,360
exchange contact information.

105
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:13,040
So cool!

106
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,640
Which young lady wrote this couplet?

107
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:16,520
Pretty impressive.

108
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,360
Let me take a photo. Come on.

109
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,840
Write a couplet, match, meet the right one.

110
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:24,880
You guys...

111
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,120
You're money-crazy.

112
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,680
I don't think it's expensive.

113
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,960
We all really like it, don't we?

114
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:32,560
Right?

115
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,160
Yeah, that's right.

116
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,160
Very creative.

117
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,400
While everyone's singing your praises,

118
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:39,560
I've got to pour some cold water on you.

119
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:43,680
This Four Treasures of the Study

120
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,320
China Chic Zone looks quite fresh.

121
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:47,800
Young people might love it.

122
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,160
But

123
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:52,040
whether provincial and city officials will like it,

124
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,680
that depends on your luck.

125
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:56,680
Director Liao, what a buzzkill.

126
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:58,360
We were all in such a good mood.

127
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:00,520
Who asked you to pour cold water on us?

128
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,320
A little cold water never hurt anyone.

129
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,680
Prepare for the worst-case scenario,

130
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:08,680
that's how you plan ahead and stay prepared.

131
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,400
It doesn't matter.

132
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,880
Do good deeds, ask not about the future.

133
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:14,280
Isn't that right, Director Liao?

134
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:17,680
Actually, most people only know the first two lines.

135
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,160
There are two more lines after that.

136
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,520
Director.

137
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:21,800
If it's good, please share.

138
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,840
If it's not, then don't bother.

139
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,320
What do you mean by good or not?

140
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:27,560
Then maybe don't say it.

141
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,360
Fine, go ahead.

142
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:31,160
Don't hold it in.

143
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:34,680
A narrow river flows fast; a desperate person finds a way.

144
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,520
If you know there's a tiger on the mountain,

145
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:39,160
don't go.

146
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,760
What a buzzkill.

147
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:43,080
Old Liao.

148
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:45,400
Secretary Peng, Secretary Peng.

149
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:47,680
To follow up on those two lines,

150
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,880
there's another one.

151
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,480
A road is cleared by walking it;

152
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,520
a task is accomplished by doing it.

153
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:53,200
Right?

154
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,680
Well, that's true.

155
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,560
Way to go, Secretary! Shut down that old pedant.

156
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:57,960
So, you see,

157
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,800
there's no right or wrong here.

158
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,480
Just follow your own hearts.

159
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:04,040
Well said, Secretary, well said.

160
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:05,560
Get back to work.

161
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,200
We won't disturb you.

162
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,160
Lin Yiran, let's go.

163
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:07,800
The Secretary said it best.

164
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:08,920
The Secretary's really something.

165
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,480
On this beautiful golden October day

166
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:34,720
Welcome, everyone, to Peach Blossom Town's

167
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:37,760
Four Treasures of the Study Festival.

168
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:39,520
All right

169
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:43,520
When brush, ink, paper, and inkstone,

170
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:46,120
gather here across a thousand years,

171
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:49,200
it's more than a showcase of traditional crafts.

172
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:52,320
It's a modern awakening of Chinese heritage.

173
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:54,360
What we're about to present

174
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:56,480
is the razor-sharp tip of the Xuan brush,

175
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:58,480
the elegant charm of Hui ink,

176
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:00,280
the endless ink variations of Xuan paper,

177
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,520
and the noble virtue of the She inkstone.

178
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,920
Behind them lies the artisans' generational

179
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,800
dedication and innovation.

180
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,920
At this Four Treasures of the Study event,

181
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,880
we'll join the masters

182
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:12,800
to decode together

183
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:15,840
the wondrous code of our cultural heritage.

184
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:20,800
This festival features three key highlights.

185
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,120
The first highlight is

186
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:25,080
gathering 42 intangible heritage workshops

187
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,560
nationwide for live demonstrations.

188
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,920
The second highlight is that

189
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:30,920
four national-level heritage inheritors,

190
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,080
who are national treasure masters,

191
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:34,320
will perform live demonstrations.

192
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,560
At two this afternoon

193
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:37,680
national ink-making master

194
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:39,200
Cheng Ruqing,

195
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:42,320
will demonstrate the ancient lamp-soot craft.

196
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,640
And the third

197
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:46,080
and biggest highlight of our inaugural festival

198
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,360
is this:

199
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:49,600
Why does our Four Treasures of the Study

200
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:52,080
festival draw so many young visitors?

201
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:54,360
It's because this festival

202
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:57,080
proudly presents the China Chic Zone.

203
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:59,000
All right

204
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:49,960
Take a look.

205
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:51,160
Who wrote this?

206
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:53,920
Come on.

207
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:02,320
Okay, okay, okay.

208
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,440
The Four Treasures of the Study.

209
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:08,560
Back when Wang Xizhi

210
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:11,080
used it to write Orchid Pavilion Preface,

211
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:13,720
it took center stage.

212
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,160
With cultural backing,

213
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:19,040
a man's handsomeness is called unrivaled elegance,

214
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:23,480
and a woman's beauty is called peerless grace.

215
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,040
I see some comments asking

216
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:26,240
what's happening behind us.

217
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:32,440
It's the Four Treasures of the Study

218
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,680
Festival performance!

219
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:34,880
Come, let me show you.

220
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:37,200
Okay.

221
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:41,320
Sis, I'm thousand-year-old pine soot

222
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:44,560
turned Little Ink Demon.

223
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:52,560
The China Chic Zone is at full capacity.

224
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,160
Don't worry, Sis Yiran.

225
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:56,400
We've got timed reservations this time.

226
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:58,200
For each person who leaves, one can enter.

227
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,560
Those who haven't gotten in

228
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,000
can wander around outside,

229
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,120
which also boosts sales.

230
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:03,320
Don't worry.

231
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,720
Why are so many people crowded at Zone A42?

232
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,480
President Xiao, President Xiao.

233
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:17,960
Please go handle Zone A42.

234
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,200
Some visitors are having a dispute.

235
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:19,880
Got it, Director Lin.

236
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:20,800
I'll handle it right away.

237
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:26,000
Hey, Old Qin.

238
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,280
Apologize to the customer immediately.

239
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,880
I know you might feel wronged,

240
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:33,520
but I've told all of you before,

241
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:36,000
if a dispute arises with a customer,

242
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:38,360
always put the customer's interests first.

243
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:38,800
Right?

244
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,600
Every one of you promised me this.

245
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:57,760
What are you doing?

246
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,160
Making paper boats.

247
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:02,080
Why didn't you come?

248
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:04,040
Xuan Bao'er's launch is this afternoon.

249
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,880
I don't like crowds.

250
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,160
Were there a lot of people?

251
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:09,280
Yes.

252
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:11,280
More than we expected.

253
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:12,880
Xuan Yan.

254
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:15,080
We did it.

255
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:17,880
No, you did it.

256
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:20,680
Remember,

257
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:21,600
once you make money,

258
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:24,160
pay me back what I fronted you.

259
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:27,760
Come on, what a buzzkill.

260
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,280
Let me tell you,

261
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:31,120
make sure that paper boat is solid.

262
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,440
If it sinks, you're in for it.

263
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:33,360
Don't worry.

264
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:34,920
No problem.

265
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,840
Okay, I'm on my way.

266
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,480
That's Sister Xiu Mei's luck.

267
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:48,200
Blessed with such a great kid.

268
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:48,800
Right.

269
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:49,840
Look at Xuan Yan,

270
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,280
that kid's got such a smart head.

271
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:52,720
Sister Xiu Mei,

272
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,920
go check out your Dayazhai booth.

273
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:55,680
Wow!

274
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:57,160
The stuff Xuan Yan designed,

275
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:59,080
people are grabbing it like it's free.

276
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,360
Free?

277
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:02,600
The stuff Xuan Yan designed

278
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:04,000
is ridiculously expensive.

279
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,800
Expensive, yes, I think so too.

280
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,120
But people are still buying.

281
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:08,200
You know what?

282
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:10,440
Online, it's selling in Beijing and Shanghai.

283
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:13,760
Look how proud this mom is.

284
